I was about to optimize a little for the custom comparator, at least for checking whether the item was previously yielded (assuming I didn't make any mistakes here):

```python
compare_to = None
try:
    if cmp_item not in seen_hashable:
        compare_to = seen_hashable
        add_using = seen_hashable.add
except TypeError:
    if cmp_item not in seen_unhashable:
        compare_to = seen_unhashable
        add_using = seen_unhashable.append

if compare_to is not None:
    unseen = True
    for seen_item in compare_to:
        if comparator(cmp_item, seen_item):
            unseen = False
            break

    if unseen:
        yield item
        add_using(cmp_item)
```

I haven't actually profiled this against the "unoptimized" custom comparator version so it might not offer much improvement but seems this version or previous would be the way to go.

