@mgorny @peterjc Here's a PR to fix this: https://github.com/peterjc/backports.lzma/pull/32  See if that works for you.

I took a look at the previous PRs and issues that lead up to this point.  The tldr; version is that the code was originally correct.

The longer explanation is that setuptools was issuing a warning about that code but setuptools has since been fixed.  The warning can still be seen on distros that use very old setuptools (RHEL6 has setuptools-0.6.10, for instance) but current setuptools does not print a warning.  The warning would only be seen when using a backports module in conjunction with pkg_resources at runtime.  The warning was harmless in this case (setuptools was not being smart enough about understanding the paths.)

To work around this issue, you can set `disable_encoding` to `True` in the selenium wire specific options you pass to the webdriver.

