Disabling CSRF isn't really a good idea. You can get the current token value like this:

from flask import jsonify
from flask.ext.security import LoginForm

@app.route('/login_csrf')
def login_csrf():
    form = LoginForm()
    return jsonify({'csrf_token': form.csrf_token.current_token})

You can then use the CSRF token that is returned as JSON in your login attempt, simply pass it as csrf_token with your email and password.

